title.narrative: REV: ADAP AND HIV/AIDS

description.narrative: REV OCT 1 2016: MENA countries have improved capacity to support sustainable and equitable opportunities at scale for civic and economic engagement of adolescent girls and boys including HIV Prevention enabling safe and productive transitions into adulthood., which contributes to Adolescent Empowerment, Adolescents And Hiv/Aids, Cross-Sectoral Adolescent Development. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Evaluations, Research And Data, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: GRP1: Governments and regional institutions in MENA benefit from UNICEF technical and other support to achieve sustainable results for children and adolescents in development and humanitarian contexts.
